    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Senna aciphylla are its antimicrobial activity, which is attributed to the presence of saponins and flavonoids that inhibit the growth of various microorganisms, and its anti-inflammatory properties, which are due to the bioactive compounds such as glycosides that reduce inflammation and pain. Senna aciphylla's antioxidant properties are mediated by the volatile oils and phenolic compounds that scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. Its laxative effects are caused by the anthraquinone glycosides, which stimulate bowel movements and relieve constipation. The diuretic property of Senna aciphylla is attributed to the presence of saponins that increase urine production and help to remove excess fluids from the body. Additionally, its antioxidant properties complement its anti-inflammatory effects, creating a synergistic effect that enhances the plant's medicinal properties.",
