    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Senna aciphylla are derived from its leaves and pods, which are rich in anthraquinone glycosides. Infusion and tea are prepared by steeping the leaves in hot water to release the active compounds, which stimulate bowel movements and relieve constipation. Decoction, made by boiling the leaves and pods, is another preparation method, often used to treat digestive issues. Tincture, a concentrated liquid extract, is prepared by soaking the leaves in a solvent, typically ethanol or glycerin, to enhance the bioavailability of the anthraquinones. Senna tea, a specific preparation made from the dried leaves of Senna aciphylla, is traditionally used to treat constipation and promote digestive health.",
